The pilot reported that while rolling out about 30 to 40 mph in the tailwheel equipped airplane 
for the full stop landing, the airplane made a sudden stop and nosed over. The airplane 
sustained substantial damage to the aft fuselage and tail section during the landing sequence. 
The passenger reported in a written statement that he accidentally applied the brakes during 
the landing roll.
The pilot reported no preimpact mechanical malfunctions or failures with the airplane that 
would have precluded normal operation.
The accidental application of the brakes by the passenger during landing roll which resulted in 
the airplane nosing over.
